=== 6.4 The Code: Scaled Dot-Product Attention in Python

Attention is a composition of named operations.
The matrix abstraction from Chapter 2 carries forward; we add multiply, transpose, scale, and add.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=matrix_ops]
----

`softmax` converts a vector of raw scores into a probability distribution.
We subtract the maximum value before exponentiating to prevent overflow.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=softmax]
----

`causal_mask` fills the upper triangle with stem:[-10^9] so future tokens cannot be attended to.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=causal_mask]
----

`scaled_dot_product_attention` and `self_attention` are direct translations of the attention formula.

